==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impenetrability
<hw>Im*pen`e*tra*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>imp⟦eacute⟧n⟦eacute⟧trabilit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Quality of being impenetrable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>That property in virtue of
which two portions of matter can not at the same time occupy the same
portion of space.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Insusceptibility of intellectual or emotional
impression; obtuseness; stupidity; coldness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impenetrable</ent>⟦br⟧
